Example
Get the total width of your screen:

Copy
let x = "Total Width: " + screen.width;

Description
The width property returns the total width of the user's screen, in pixels.

Use the height property to get the total height of the user's screen.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
width	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
let a = screen.width;
Return Value
A Number, representing the total width of the user's screen, in pixels.
